# T14-tv-lid-closed — lid CLOSED, TV over HDMI only.
# autorandr matches profiles by EDID (the 'setup' file), so this profile
# must be saved on the T14 with the TV connected and the laptop panel off.
# It cannot be fabricated. autorandr ignores this file (only 'config', 'setup',
# and hook scripts matter), so it is safe here as a reminder.
#
# Layout: TV primary, laptop panel off.
#
# 1. Connect the TV, set the layout (eDP off simulates lid closed):
#      xrandr --output HDMI-1 --primary --auto --output eDP-1 --off
#
# 2. Save (writes real 'config' + 'setup' here):
#      autorandr --save T14-tv-lid-closed
#
# 3. Copy back into the repo (live dir is a throwaway stow copy):
#      cp -r ~/.config/autorandr/T14-tv-lid-closed ~/environment/dotfiles/config/.config/autorandr/
#
# 4. Commit.
